# Observability Provider Abstraction Rules

## Intent
Enable provider-neutral error monitoring so Sentry can be used now and Signoz can be adopted later with minimal refactoring.

## Mandatory
- All error capture must flow through a shared provider-agnostic interface.
- Feature modules must never call vendor SDKs directly.
- Use normalized event shape (`message`, `level`, `tags`, `context`, `fingerprint`, `timestamp`).
- Support provider routing by configuration (Sentry, Signoz, no-op).

## Migration Safety Rules
- Keep adapter contracts stable even if provider changes.
- Implement provider adapters in dedicated integration modules only.
- Preserve privacy scrubbing before provider handoff regardless of provider.

## Operational Rules
- Initialize provider once per runtime boundary.
- Fail open to no-op reporting if provider config is missing, while preserving local logging.
- Track provider health and dropped-event metrics.
- Use rewrite-specific DSNs/config and keep them isolated from legacy project telemetry.
- Configure provider by environment variables:
	- Web: `NEXT_PUBLIC_OBSERVABILITY_PROVIDER`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN`
	- Mobile: `EXPO_PUBLIC_OBSERVABILITY_PROVIDER`, `EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN`

## Prohibited
- Embedding provider-specific APIs into domain/business logic.
- Duplicating vendor-specific capture code across web and mobile features.
